---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <h2>Some of my favorite ..</h2>

  <h3>Youtube Channels</h3>
    <div class="articles">
      <article>
        <h4>
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@KevinPowell/videos">Kevin Powell</a>
        </h4>
        <p>
          If you don't know who Kevin Powell is, I'm afraid you're on your own
          here.
        </p>
        <div class="tags"><span class="tag">CSS</span></div>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h4>
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@JoyofCodeDev/videos">Joy of Code</a>
        </h4>
        <p>
          Joy of Code has a ton of videos where they show you some cool things you can do with Sveltekit. They also have a<a href="https://joyofcode.xyz/"> digital garden</a> where you can find many blog posts and resouces for everything webdev!
        <br>
        They recently uploaded a video, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=afLUZz_7ySc&t=925s">7 Projects to Learn Svelte 5</a>, which I will definitely be trying out soon!
        </p>
        <div class="tags"><span class="tag">CSS</span></div>
      </article>
  

      <article>
        <h4>
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@Fireship/videos">Fireship</a>
        </h4>
        <p>
          Fireship posts tutorials, videos about current events in the frontend
          world, and random stuff that has to do with frontend.
          <br />
           They also have their own website with written tutorials and courses,
          which is built with Svelte - yay!
        </p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Javascript</span>
          <span class="tag">Tutorials</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h4>
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@t3dotgg/videos">Theo - t3.gg</a>
        </h4>
        <p>
          Theo makes videos about current events in the frontend world, new and
          upcoming JS features, and frameworks, mostly Next and React. In the
          description he links his sources, so you can read where he got the
          info from, and dive deeper if you want.
        </p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Javascript</span>
          <span class="tag">Frameworks</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h4>
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@juxtopposed/videos">Juxtopposed</a>
        </h4>
        <p>
          Juxtopossed mostly uploads videos of redesigns of well known apps and
          websites, focused on UI and UX. She also created <a
            href="https://www.realtimecolors.com/?colors=050315-fbfbfe-2f27ce-dedcff-433bff&fonts=Inter-Inter"
            >Realtime Colors</a
          >, a tool to help you pick good looking and accessible colors for your
          design.
        </p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Design</span>
          <span class="tag">UX</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <h3>Blogs and social accounts</h3>
    <div class="articles">
      <article>
        <h4>
          <a href="https://web.dev/blog">web.dev</a>
        </h4>
        <p>The latest news and updates.</p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Design</span>
          <span class="tag">UX</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h4>
          <a href="https://www.bram.us/">Bramus</a>
        </h4>
        <p>
          Bramus is a webdeveloper, working at Google. He has build <a
            href="https://scroll-driven-animations.style/"
            >scroll-driven-animations.style</a
          >, a super handy website for scroll driven animations, which I have
          used a ton.
          <br />
           I also recommend following him on <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bramus/">LinkedIn</a
          >, here he shares more useful bits of frontend knowledge.
        </p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Design</span>
          <span class="tag">UX</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    @media (min-width: 768px) {
      .articles {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
        align-items: stretch;
        gap: 1rem;
      }
    }

    article {
      display: grid;
      min-height: 17rem;
      max-width: 26rem;
      grid-template-rows: 15% 65% 20%;
      grid-template-areas:
        "title"
        "description"
        "tags";
      margin: 0.5rem 0 1.5rem 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      list-style: "";
      border-left: 6px solid var(--primary);
    }

    h4 {
      grid-area: title;
      color: var(--primary);
      font-size: larger;
    }

    h4 a {
      align-self: self-start;
      color: var(--primary);
    }

    p {
      grid-area: description;
      align-self: flex-start;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--primary);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a::before {
      content: "ðŸ”—";
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      vertical-align: middle;
      margin-right: 0.2rem;
      text-decoration:;
    }

    h4 a::before {
      content: "";
      margin: 0rem;
    }

    .tags {
      grid-area: tags;
      align-self: flex-end;
    }

    .tag {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      background-color: var(--accent-two);
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 0.25rem;
      margin-right: 0.25rem;
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
      article {
        animation: linear animate-in-and-out;
        animation-timeline: view();
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
